  "instructions": [
    "In a ttukbaegi earthenware pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the shrimp and cook until pink, about 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Add the tangy apple cider vinegar, apple cider, black pepper, and salt. Stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 5-7 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Stir in the breadcrumbs and cook for another minute, until crispy.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with parsley and lemon wedges on the side.",
    "Serve immediately, and enjoy!"
